80377>>>Use StatusPanel.pkg
Including file: StatusPanel.pkg    (C:\Projects\DF18\DbUpdateFramework\AppSrc\StatusPanel.pkg)
80377>>>>>// StatPnl.pkg - creates the standard status_panel object.
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// This is the default Status Panel object used by any of the Visual DataFlex classes that
80377>>>>>// invoke the standard status panel. The standard has always been that the package name
80377>>>>>// is StatPnl.pkg and the name of the object is Status_Panel. As of 12.0, there are major
80377>>>>>// changes in the way the status panel operates The Sentinel based external status panel used in
80377>>>>>// prior revisions has been replace with status panel that is part of the application.
80377>>>>>// This should work much better and faster than the old sentinel based solution.
80377>>>>>// While the way this operates has changed, the interface has not and therefore this should work
80377>>>>>// with most applications.
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// As of 12.0, we have added a global handle that contains the object ID of this status panel.
80377>>>>>// This variable ghoStatusPanel can be used in place of the object name Status_Panel. This provides
80377>>>>>// a cleaner more robust interface.
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// Compatibility Note:
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// When used in the standard way, this change will require no changes. A developer will only need to
80377>>>>>// change their code if they've modified the sentinel program, which was a difficult thing to do.
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// If for some reason you application will not work using this as a replacement for the old status
80377>>>>>// panel, you've probably done something special with the old status-panel. If you don't want to
80377>>>>>// figure out how to use the new one and you want to continue using the old one you are going to need
80377>>>>>// to add some code to include the old status panel in your application. Add the following to your project (your src).
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// Use StatPnl.pkg    // Make sure you load the new status panel object first. this is not optional!
80377>>>>>// Use OldStatPnl.pkg // load the old status panel. Status_Panel is now this old object
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// If you do this, you will lose access to the new status-panel via Status_Panel. However, you
80377>>>>>// can still access the new object via the ghoStatusPanel handle.
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// Creating your own Status Panel objects
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// If a developer wishes to create a custom panel, they should use this package as their template.
80377>>>>>// This panel can be visually modeled and changed any way you wish. Just save your new custom panel
80377>>>>>// with a different file and object name and direct your status panel request to the new object.
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// If the new panel changes the interface and updates objects that are not currently defined, you
80377>>>>>// want to make sure you send the message ProcessEvents after you've updated the object. This allows
80377>>>>>// the object to paint when inside of a tight loop. For example, if you wanted to add a progress
80377>>>>>// bar (cProgressBar) you would want to Send ProcessEvents after you update the progress bar.
80377>>>>>// e.g.
80377>>>>>//       Procedure UpdateStatusBar
80377>>>>>//           Send DoAdvance of oProgressBar
80377>>>>>//           Send ProcessEvents
80377>>>>>//       End_Procedure
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// of course, if you use the standard interfaces in status bar and your forward send these
80377>>>>>// messages this will be done for you.
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// the standard Interface for status panels are:
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// Send Initialize_StatusPanel - initializes values for caption, title & message
80377>>>>>// Send Start_StatusPanel      - start the status panel
80377>>>>>// Send Stop_StatusPanel       - stop the status panel
80377>>>>>// Send Update_StatusPanel     - update the status panel's action area
80377>>>>>// Get  Check_StatusPanel      - check for cancel (if cancel or pbCancel is set, close the panel)
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// Get/Set Caption_Text - updates the caption bar
80377>>>>>// Get/Set Title_Text   - updates the title area
80377>>>>>// Get/Set Message_Text - updates the Message area
80377>>>>>// Get/Set Action_Text  - updates the action area
80377>>>>>// Get/Set Button_Text  - updates the button area
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// Get/Set Allow_cancel_state - determines if panel can be canceled
80377>>>>>// Send EnableCancelButton - code you should provide to enable/disable cancel button
80377>>>>>//
80377>>>>>// ghoStatusPanel - global handle that points to the standard status panel.
80377>>>>>Use cProcessStatusPanel.pkg
